summary: An ordinance accepting a deed to the City of Seattle executed on July 16, 1910, by the Seattle Southeastern Railway Company by its President, John Bagley, and its Secretary, E. M. Hayden, for lands in Section 18, 19, 20, 21, 22, 27, 28, 29, 30, 31, 32, 33, 34 and 35, Township 22 North, Range 8 East, W.M., King County, State of Washington.
